HBA Calls for Volunteers - Your Help is Needed

The HBA needs volunteer attorneys to help answer legal questions and provide
general guidance to members of the public dealing with the aftermath of
recent flooding.  Your help is needed to staff special LegalLine Sessions,
to respond to phone calls received through the SBOT/HBA hot line and to
provide information at relief centers.  The HBA is accepting volunteers with
hours or days to contribute.  Read on for further details about these
volunteer opportunities and to learn about training opportunities.

Special LegalLine:
When:
		Thursday, June 28, 2001  --  4:45 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. and from
6:45 p.m. to 9:00 p.m.

Thursday, July 12, 2001   --  4:45 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. and from 6:45 p.m. to
9:00 p.m.

Thursday, July 26, 2001   --  4:45 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. and from 6:45 p.m. to
9:00 p.m.

Thursday, August 9, 2001 --  4:45 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. and from 6:45 p.m. to
9:00 p.m.

		Thursday, August 23, 2001 --  4:45 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. and
from 6:45 p.m. to 9:00 p.m.

		 Attorneys may volunteer for one or more shifts.
Where:
HBA offices, 1001 Fannin, Suite 1300
Other:
Resource materials will be provided. Volunteers from past flood LegalLine
Programs have answered questions involving landlord/tenant issues, consumer
law, insurance matters and other areas of the law. Attorneys do not provide
their identities to callers.

To Schedule Volunteer Service or for further information:
