Information Booths and Town Meetings:
When:
As requested by FEMA and other relief agencies.  We anticipate a time
commitment of from 1-3 hours once the attorney is on site.

Where:
FEMA Disaster Recovery Centers.  Locations will vary.

Other:
Resource materials will be provided. Volunteers should anticipate questions
involving landlord/tenant issues, consumer law, insurance matters and other
areas of the law.

To Schedule Volunteer Service or for further information:
E-mail kays@hba.org or contact Kay Sim at 713/759-1133

Training:
Information concerning the time and location of training sessions will be
posted on the HBA Web site at http://www.hba.org and  may be obtained by
calling the HBA at (713) 759-1133. Training will cover a variety of legal
issues including but not limited to landlord/tenant, consumer protection,
insurance, employment law and lost documents.  MCLE credit is being applied
for from the State Bar of Texas.



Thank you for volunteering,

